{
  "text": "The only usable (unclipped) T-wave record available for processing is that at Afareaitu (AFR), on the island of Moorea. We were unable to detect T waves above the noise level on the WWSSN records at Kipapa, Oahu, nor at Haleakala, Maui, a station that prominently recorded those of the mainshock and of other, smaller, aftershocks. As a reference event, we use the smaller nearby event of 1976 January 21 for which a CMT solution (M 0 = 6.9 × 10 26 dyn cm) is available [CITATION_1] . Fig. 6 clearly shows the weak amplitude and long duration of the T waves of the 1963 aftershock, and as detailed in Table 6 , the deficiency in for the tsunami earthquake, relative to the 1976 event, reaches 300.",
